], "ailments_description": "The most common ailments you can heal with Roldana sinuata are eczema, a skin condition characterized by inflammation and itching, and wounds, which the plant's antimicrobial properties help to heal by preventing bacterial growth and promoting tissue repair. Roldana sinuata also effectively treats fever, a condition where the body temperature is elevated, often due to infection or illness, by reducing inflammation and promoting sweating. Additionally, the plant's antiseptic and anti-inflammatory properties make it useful for treating infections and abscesses, often caused by bacterial or fungal growth. Furthermore, Roldana sinuata's astringent properties help to reduce swelling and promote healing in cases of conjunctivitis, an eye infection that causes redness and discharge. By reducing inflammation and promoting tissue repair, Roldana sinuata can also aid in the recovery from sprains and strains, common injuries that occur when ligaments or muscles are stretched or torn.", "properties": [{"name": "antioxidant", "mentions": 20, "confidence_score": 153, "total_score": 3060}, {"name": "antimicrobial", "mentions": 20, "confidence_score": 146, "total_score": 2920}, {"name": "anti-inflammatory", "mentions": 20, "confidence_score": 142, "total_score": 2840}, {"name": "analgesic", "mentions": 20, "confidence_score": 87, "total_score": 1740}, {"name": "antifungal", "mentions": 13, "confidence_score": 80, "total_score": 1040}, {"name": "antibacterial", "mentions": 9, "confidence_score": 72, "total_score": 648}, {"name": "hepatoprotective", "mentions": 11, "confidence_score": 68, "total_score": 748}, {"name": "antiviral", "mentions": 11, "confidence_score": 51, "total_score": 561}, {"name": "cardioprotective", "mentions": 11, "confidence_score": 50, "total_score": 550}, {"name": "antispasmodic", "mentions": 8, "confidence_score": 48, "total_score": 384}, {"name": "antihistamine", "mentions": 6, "confidence_score": 25, "total_score": 150}, {"name":